Post-Match Reflections: José Ramírez expressed determination to achieve the 40-40-40 milestone next year despite the cancellation of Game 162.
Guardians manager Stephen Vogt reflected on Ramírez's impressive season and his near 40-40-40 achievement.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The final game of the regular season between the Cleveland Guardians and Houston Astros was canceled due to inclement weather and field conditions.
Fans will receive a credit for their tickets that can be used toward a 2024 postseason game or a regular-season contest in 2025.
The game was not necessary for either team as both had already secured their respective seeds in the AL playoff bracket.
